How it is working:

• User A wants to know a User B location.

• User A enters the phone number of User B into the app.

• The app generates a unique URL, and the URL is sent to User B.

• If User B clicks on the link, user A will see the location of user B.

Limitations:

• This is not a spy app. User B must agree to share the location with you.

• If User B has a device without GPS (desktop computer, tablet), the determined location may have a large accuracy margin (up to 5 km).

• In rare situations, when user B is behind the corporate proxy, the app can show the proxy's location, not the user's.

The user location is determined in three ways:

• E.123, E.164
• RIR
• W3C Geolocation API

The app provides digital readouts of values that would otherwise have to be eyeballed in a standard E6B.  The use of cursors and steppers enables the precision of a digital computer with the speed and intuitiveness of an analog computer.

The E6B is an analog computer invented in the 1930's by Lt. Philip Dalton, USN for purposes of training and flight calculations.  

The app can be used to perform calculations, or to practice and learn how to use a mechanical E6B.

Advantages of analog slide-rule E6Bs include the speed of entering data, and continous operation that can enable a more intuitive feel for how outputs change as inputs are changed.  If inputs are changed, it is simply a matter of a swipe or using a stepper to fine tune inputs, and outputs are updated simultaneously.

Advantages of digital E6B's includes precision, but as E6Bs are in reality often used to estimate data, this precision often cannot be taken advantage of.  Furthermore, entering data is slowed down by soft keypads popping up and down.  It may be hard to understand how outputs change in response to inputs if individual numbers need to be entered on a keypad.

Sparky's E6B provides the best of both worlds.  The speed and intuitive entry of an analog E6B, along with the digital readout of a digital E6B.

The "slide rule" or "front" side includes a circular log-log scale that can be used for multiplication, division, fuel consumption and time/speed/distance calculations.  There are also various conversions available, such as nautical-miles/statute-miles/kilometers, fuel and oil volume and weight.  The windows on the front are used for airspeed, various forms of "altitude' and mach number calculations.

Ans: After accepting request, FATHER(Consider above example to understand) will get,
His daughter is ideal or moving. If moving then what is her speed, Her Exact Location, Timestamp, Device name from where her daughter accessing/Logged in this app, Heading, Accuracy of location, and altitude.

2. How many members can I include for tracking?
Ans: You can track 2 members for FREE and then you need to buy package as per member requirements. Currently 3 pack is available  for 5/7/10 member track request in minimum cost.  

3. How to use it? 
You need to create your own account and share your QR / User Id to whom you allow to track access your location. Same way you need to scan QR / user Id of your family members to get access of their latest location.

4. How to get my UserId / QR?
Login with your account > Go to Profile Screen > Go To 'Your QR' Screen. Here is your own QR and user Id below it. You can Copy user Id OR save QR to local storage also.

5. How To track my family member?
Install this app to all device you want to track and create individual login credentials. Login with your own account > Go To 'Profile' Screen > Go To 'Track By You' Screen > Click On Top Right QR Scan Button to Scan your family member QR or enter their user id manually. (You can track maximum 2 members for free. You can buy track pack based on member requirements.)

6. I need help / support from technical side.
Ans: Go to help center, You can directly Email to developer OR visit our web site. Or you also can join social page to discuss your problem.
